## Status Labels

Use these consistently so heartbeat instances can triage quickly:

- **(ACTIVE)** — Work is happening. Next steps are clear.
- **(ONGOING)** — No fixed endpoint. Background activity.
- **(BLOCKED)** — Waiting on something external. Name the blocker explicitly.
- **(DONE)** — Completed. Keep briefly for context, then archive.
- **(STALE)** — No progress in 5+ beats. Either reactivate with a concrete next step or mark blocked/done.

When an objective is blocked, decompose the blocker: what parts can be done offline? What requires human decision? What requires an external dependency to resolve? Blocked objectives that can be partially decomposed should list the offline-viable slices as next steps.

